* * Template for a DMR address which might contain multiple variable parts. * * An address template can be defined using the following BNF: * 
 * <address template> ::= "/" | <segment>
 * <segment>          ::= <tuple> | <segment>"/"<tuple>
 * <tuple>            ::= <variable> | <key>"="<value>
 * <variable>         ::= "{"<alpha>"}"
 * <key>              ::= <alpha>
 * <value>            ::= <variable> | <alpha> | "*"
 * <alpha>            ::= <upper> | <lower>
 * <upper>            ::= "A" | "B" | … | "Z"
 * <lower>            ::= "a" | "b" | … | "z"
 *
* * Following variables are supported: * - {domain.controller} * - {selected.profile} * - {selected.group} * - {selected.server-config} * - {selected.server} * * To get a fully qualified address from an address template use the method resolve(). For standalone mode * the variables will resolve to an empty string. The values of the variables are managed by the {@link * StatementContext}. * * @example AddressTemplate a2 = AddressTemplate.of("{selected.profile}"); * AddressTemplate a3 = AddressTemplate.of("{selected.profile}/subsystem=mail"); * AddressTemplate a4 = AddressTemplate.of("{selected.profile}/subsystem=mail/mail-session=*");
